OL,6,FThe governor's indication that lower
OL,7,Flending rates and reduced inflation
OL,8,Fcould be around the corner comes as
OL,9,Fthe Government is facing pressure to
OL,10,Fimprove living standards.
OL,12,FMs Reeves' tax and spend plans are
OL,13,Falso being constrained by the current
OL,14,Fborrowing costs, as well as downgraded
OL,15,Fgrowth forecasts.
OL,17,FThe Chancellor's fiscal headroom has
OL,18,Fbeen in part eroded by U-turns on the
OL,19,Fwinter fuel payment and welfare
OL,20,Freforms, as well as global shocks to
OL,21,Fthe British economy.
